      <custodhist id="aspace_691cf6ca8401b23949eedac7b425b13e">
         <head>Custodial History note</head>
         <p>Lycurgus Davey, a neurosurgeon and member of the Yale Medical faculty, was a graduate of Yale College (1939) and Yale School of Medicine (1943). These letters were probably lent by Lucia Fulton to Dr. Davey who wrote historical articles on Fulton.</p>  
      </custodhist>
